<DOC><DOCNO> AP880902-0131 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-02-88 1400EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a AM-BRF--RavioliAccident     09-02 0163</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Ravioli Accident,0168</SECOND><HEAD>Ravioli Factory Machine Swallows Man</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A ravioli factory employee was pulledinto a dough-kneading machine, and rescuers had to bring themachine to the hospital along with the man, authorities said.   Calvin Knight of Mount Vernon was in stable condition Friday.   Knight had disappeared completely in the six-foot-tall machineThursday at John's Ravioli Co., said Fire Commissioner RaymondKiernan.   Kiernan said rescuers had to work for more than an hour beforeKnight and the machine could be transported to New RochelleHospital, where the blades used to knead the dough were removed.   Knight underwent surgery and may regain most of the use of hisright arm, a spokeswoman at New Rochelle Hospital said.   Henry Guanero, an employee at the factory, said Knight wascleaning his machine at the end of the day when the accidentoccurred.   Neither factory officials nor the police were able to determineexactly why Knight was pulled into the machine.</TEXT></DOC>